latestIgtvVideos.title: Lag ja gale♥️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I know this is not my best attempt, but when I hear this song I get super emotional, the lyrics make me sad and happy at the same time and I know this song is special for everyone out here. .
'Phir aapke Naseeb me ye baat ho na ho' 
Damn, Everytime you play this song, a certain someone will come to your mind, it can be anyone! & you know you secretly pray for their happyness. You simply don't need words to express your love. Just close your eyes and wait for the lyrics to get into your nerves and calm you down with love and hope! ♥️
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
One year ago today, I arrived in the UK, my first time ever being away from home. From navigating a new country with maps to now knowing places by heart, from the anxiety of my first day at uni to seeing my work featured on displays and invites, it’s been an incredible journey. What started as uncertainty has turned into a sense of belonging, with friends who feel like family. It’s been a rollercoaster of emotions, but I’ve enjoyed every moment. I miss my home and loved ones, but this experience has been so rewarding. Living in a foreign country has taught me so much, and stepping into another year, I’m filled with even more passion, hope, and excitement! Here’s to another chapter! please treat me well UK! 🥺♥️🌸
.
.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Onto next chapter!!! 👩‍🎓🧿💯

Coming here and completing my Master’s degree was a dream! I worked very hard to make it happen, to step into this country and despite all the hurdles, we made it, we go harddd!! Along the way, I met some amazing people, made lifelong friends, and collaborated with incredible talents, each with their own inspiring stories! BCU has given me some nice memories that I’ll cherish forever, and to everyone out there, away from home, chasing their dreams, and making their mark, y’all deserve the world! Cheers to new beginnings and the journey ahead! 🥂✨
